                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-617" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS CLAYDON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a bricklayer, and live in Salmon's-lane, Limehouse. At twelve o'clock on the 19th of April, the prisoner came and hired a truck of me—I found it at John Dudley's, the green-grocer—it was the one that I had let him—he had it for an hour.</p>
